<h1>Project Highlights</h1>

<h3>1. Planning, Contracting, and Mobilization of 1,500 HP Land Rig to Drill Umuseti-2 Well for Pillar Oil</h3>
<p>Well drilled to 10,700 ft and completed with dual 3-1/2” tubing.</p>

<h3>2. Planning, Contracting, and Mobilization of Jack-Up Rig to Drill a Sidetrack for Shebah E&P</h3>
<p>Well drilled to 10,500 ft and completed with 4-1/2” slotted liner, 4-1/2” tubing, and retrievable ESP.</p>

<h3>3. Carrying Out Feasibility, Preparing Drilling Program, and Contracts for the Drilling of Seme Well for SAPETRO</h3>

<h3>4. Planning and Supervision of Addax Jackup Rig Drilling Operations</h3>
<p>(Kita Marine Platform-B Development, Adanga North, Oron Projects, Okwok, etc.) using splitter wellheads; and deep water offshore operations (Ofrima project).</p>

<h3>5. Planning and Supervision of Deep Offshore Drilling Operations in SNEPCO (Bonga Project)</h3>

<h3>6. Planning, Contracting, and Supervision of 2,000 HP Land Rig to Drill 4 Wells for Midwestern Oil & Gas Ltd.</h3>
<p>One horizontal well drilled to 11,000 ft and completed with 4-1/2” tubing.</p>
<p>Two vertical wells drilled to 10,500 and 11,300 ft respectively and completed with dual 3-1/2” & 2-7/8” tubing.</p>
<p>One water injector well drilled to 6,000 ft with 4-1/2” completion.</p>
<p>Drove down well cost by +/-20% over the 4 well campaign.</p>

<h3>7. Planning, Contracting, and Mobilization of 2,000 HP Swamp Rig for the Akaso Development for Eroton EP</h3>

<h3>8. Planning and Supervision of Pioneer Natural Resources Deepwater GOM Operations</h3>
<p>(Flying Cloud and Clipper, GOM) and Kosmos Energy (Echim Project, Deepwater Nigeria).</p>

<h3>9. Planning, Contracting, and Supervision of the Revamping of Saltpond Field Offshore Ghana</h3>
<p>After more than 15 years of inactivity:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Refurbished, upgraded, and converted abandoned dilapidated offshore jack-up drilling rig to a production facility.</li>
  <li>Re-entered, worked over, and recompleted 3 out of 6 suspended wells.</li>
  <li>Set up logistics base and administrative office, recruited, and trained local personnel.</li>
  <li>Put field to production and maintained +/- 1,500 BOPD for over eight years.</li>
  <li>Commissioned field reserves evaluation and mapped out strategy for drilling and producing the untested reserves in the deeper part of the field.</li>
  <li>Managed the crude sales agreement and set up offshore crude oil terminal.</li>
  <li>Liaised with Ghana National Petroleum Corporation and Ministry of Energy for necessary approvals and permits.</li>
</ul>

<h3>10. Planning, Contracting, and Supervision of the Decommissioning of the Saltpond Field, Offshore Ghana (Ongoing)</h3>
<p>Partnering with a Ghanaian company to prepare the technical presentations to Ghana National Petroleum Corporation on the Decommissioning Strategy.</p>
<p>Prequalified subcontractors, collated their inputs and prepared the bid document in line with tender requirement to plug and abandon 6 wells and dismantle and dispose of the dilapidated production platform on a turnkey basis.</p>
<p>Followed up with clarification and necessary actions to win the bid.</p>
<p>Prepared all contracts, provided all regulatory documentation, mobilized Shelf Drilling’s Trident-08 Jack-up rig and all service contractors from Nigeria to Ghana to commence operations.</p>
<p>Operations commenced in October 2022, completed 5 out of 6 wells within 6 months against a plan of 9 months.</p>
<p>Mobilized jack-up barge, LB Fugar, in December 2022 for the dismantling of the converted production platform from the site.</p>

